	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The US power supply should be fine, as has been said, the NES just needs 9V.  I live in the UK but have a US NTSC NES (technically a US NES mainboard in the old case - I wanted to play games at full 60Hz, can't imagine wanting to go the other way!), and the power supply I had for my old UK PAL NES works absolutely fine with it.<br /><br />I'd heard Vizio TVs are pretty handy when it comes to PAL/NTSC support, they're decent for the price.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
