		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">neshiggins wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I wanted to play games at full 60Hz, can't imagine wanting to go the other way!</div><br />Some NES games' vblank routines require the longer vertical blank period of the PAL NES. (Asterix anyone?) And a developer might want to test on a 50 Hz console in order to make a game that adapts its music and game speed to 50 Hz as Codemasters games do.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


